<section class="event-info">
	<div class="container">
		<div class="event-time">
			<h1>Thursday, April 25, 2013 @ 1:00pm (MST)</h1>
			<h3>Watch it LIVE in the new <%= link_to "H&S Virtual Garage", new_user_registration_path %>.</h3>
		</div>

		<hr />

		<div class="event-desc">
			<h5>In order for us here at H&amp;S to continue to design innovative products, every now and then
			we need to push a test vehicle to its absolute limits; we need to find its Breaking Point.</h5>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

<section class="recap" id="recap">
	<div class="container">
		<div class="row">
			<div class="offset6 span6">
				<div class="section-heading">
					<h2>Breaking Point 1 Recap</h2>
					<h4>Ford 6.7L, a new level of respect</h4>
				</div>
				<div class="section-body">
					<p>The first Breaking Point was completely jaw-dropping. We took a stock Ford 6.7L Scorpion engine, bolted on a few parts from
					H&amp;S Motorsports, and hit 884 horsepower before the transmission slipped.</p>

					<div class="play-video-btn">
						<a class="play-video ss-icon ss-standard" data-toggle="lightbox" href="#playVideo">play</a>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

<section class="the-truck" id="truck">
	<div class="container">
		<div class="row">
			<div class="offset1 span6">
					<div class="section-heading inner">
					<h2>The Truck</h2>
					<h4>LML: A chance to prove itself</h4>
				</div>

				<div class="section-body">
					<p>Now that we have a better idea of what the Scorpion is capable of, it's time to move on and give the GM crowd
					some love. We've seen a lot of posts on our <a href="https://www.facebook.com/hsperformance?fref=ts" target="_blank">Facebook</a> page and heard endless chatter about the LML far out-performing
					the Scorpion. Is all the talk legit? I guess we'll see. We don't really care who 'wins', we just need to see what the Duramax can do.</p>
					<%= link_to "Get the specs on our LML Duramax 6.6L", new_user_registration_path, :class => "btn btn-success" %>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

